{
  "texts": [
    "The U-Net architecture has direct skip connections between the encoder and decoder that helps in extracting and reconstructing the image features.",
    "Generative adversarial network (GAN) was first introduced in 2014 by Goodfellow et al. (51).",
    "It improved the quality of image generation as compared to the previous Convolution Neural Network (CNN) models.",
    "The architecture of GAN as shown in Figure 5 trains two separate neural networks, the generator (G) and the discriminator (D).",
    "G attempts to create synthetic images while D on the other side decides if that image looks like the real image or not (52, 53)."
  ]
}